parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
and the vehicle may not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the acceleration system can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy

the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coolant expansion tank can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Coolant leaks from the middle seam of the reservoir tank or top hose connection
smoke coming from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injector can cause the engine to misfire, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: warning that power may be lost.
